  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(37) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "If I do not the works of my Father.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—He has met the charge of blasphemy on technical grounds. In this and the following verse He advances from that defence to the ultimate test. Whether He is a blasphemer or not depends upon whether He represents God or not, and to prove this He appeals again to the works. Are they or are they not the works of the Father? (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 10:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 5:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 5:36",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 9:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 14:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
