        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " by which he doth not only mean works that are pleasing and acceptable to God, as acts of obedience to the will of God performed by men may be called, and are, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "John 6:28,29",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 6:28",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ",29",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; nor (as I conceive) only those works which he did by commission and authority from his Father, which, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "John 17:4",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 17:4",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", he calleth the work which his Father had given him to do; but those works which none but God could do; such were the multiplication of the loaves, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "John 6:1-14",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
