            "text": "John 6:1-14",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the curing of him who was born blind, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "John 9:1-41",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 9:1-41",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", &c. If (saith our Saviour) I do not do those works which no mere man ever did, give me no credit; but if I do those works which can be done by no human art or power, you have reason to believe me. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
